INSERT INTO site_settings (key, value, category) 
VALUES (
  'service_proprietorship-registration_rich_content', 
  '<h3>Who is this for</h3><p>If you are a freelancer, consultant, tutor, photographer, designer, or running any kind of solo operation and people are paying you for it, you are already a proprietorship. You just are not registered as one. That gap between operating informally and being legally recognized costs you more than you think: clients who ask for a GST invoice and walk away when you cannot provide one, banks that will not open a current account without business proof, and government tenders you cannot even apply for. Proprietorship registration fixes that. It is the simplest, most affordable business structure in India and the most common starting point for solo professionals who are serious about what they do.</p><h3>What exactly is a Proprietorship</h3><p>A sole proprietorship is a business owned and operated by a single individual with no legal distinction between the owner and the business. You are the business. There is no separate company, no board, no partners. Every rupee of profit is yours and every liability is yours too. It does not get registered through a single government portal the way a Private Limited company does. Instead, legitimacy comes from a combination of registrations: a trade license from your local municipal body, GST registration if your turnover crosses ₹20 lakh or you serve clients outside your state, an MSME/Udyam certificate for government recognition, and a current account in your business name. Together these documents establish your business as real, operational, and compliant.</p><h3>The difficulty of doing it yourself</h3><p>It is not impossible. But it is genuinely tedious and the process is fragmented across multiple portals, offices, and document requirements that vary by state and city. Getting a trade license means visiting your local municipal corporation, understanding which category your business falls under, submitting the right forms with address proof, identity proof, and photographs, and then waiting. The timeline and requirements differ between Jaipur, Delhi, Mumbai, and every other city. GST registration is done online through the GST portal and is relatively straightforward if your documents are clean and your business category is clear. The complications arise when your address proof does not match exactly, when you pick the wrong business category, or when your application gets flagged for verification. Rectifying a rejected GST application adds weeks. MSME registration through the Udyam portal is the easiest part and genuinely self-serviceable. Opening a current account requires walking into a bank with your trade license, GST certificate, address proof, and PAN. The real cost of doing it yourself is not money. It is three to six weeks of back and forth, half days lost at government offices, and the anxiety of not knowing if you have done it correctly.</p><h3>What you walk away with</h3><p>A trade license in your business name. GST registration and your GSTIN. An MSME/Udyam certificate. Guidance on opening a current account. And the confidence of knowing it was done correctly the first time.</p><h3>One thing to know before you start</h3><p>A proprietorship offers no liability protection. If your business incurs a debt or faces a legal claim, your personal assets are at risk. For most solo service professionals starting out this is an acceptable trade-off given the simplicity and low cost. But if you are handling client money, signing large contracts, or building something you plan to scale with partners or funding, a Private Limited company or LLP is worth considering from the start. We will tell you this honestly in your discovery call. We would rather you choose the right structure than pay us twice.</p>', 
  'services'
) ON CONFLICT (key) DO UPDATE SET value = EXCLUDED.value;
